I recently hosted my 40th Birthday Dinner at Da Nonna Rosa. They have private rooms on the second floor with ample space for an intimate gathering or parties up to 80-90 people. This is a hard review for me to write.  I've eaten at Da Nonna Rosa many times over the last few years and always had a good meal with pleasant service. This time, however,  my wife's food had an incredibly long hair in it. Fortunately,  it didn't wind up on her fork. We called over the waiter, who offered to replace both of our plates. We, however,  had lost our appetites at that point.  The manager offered to comp the meal,  but we insisted on paying for the appetizer we ate. They gave us a gift card, but I doubt we will be back. This is the only incident I have heard of at this restaurant,  but it was very offputting.  Kitchen hygiene is essential.
